This paper deals with clustering of high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data analysis. The use of independent component analysis (ICA) and functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) suggests a focus on neuroscience and medical imaging, which could lead to the categories of cs.NE and cs.CV. The use of dimensionality reduction and spectral clustering suggests a focus on unsupervised learning and clustering, which could lead to the categories of cs.LG and cs.SI. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques in the context of fMRI data analysis suggests a focus on applications of machine learning, which could lead to the category of cs.AI.
